  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1021",
  "title": "Release script failing on Travis",
  "body": "I tried to release the 1.5.1 version using the `npm run release` but the [Travis build on master](https://travis-ci.org/algolia/instantsearch.js/builds/130811740) kept failing.\n\nHere is the error:\n\n```\nnpm prune\nnpm run shrinkwrap --dev\n> instantsearch.js@1.5.1 shrinkwrap /home/travis/build/algolia/instantsearch.js\n> npm-shrinkwrap --dev\nProblems were encountered\nPlease correct and try again.\ninvalid: babel-runtime@6.6.1 /home/travis/build/algolia/instantsearch.js/node_modules/babel-runtime\nsomething went wrong. Did not write npm-shrinkwrap.json\n```\n\nI restarted the build and it failed again. I tried to replicate on my machine using the same node and npm version and the `shrinkwrap` worked perfectly. I even globally installed `npm@2` to be sure to have the same one.\n\nSo in the end the tag was already created and picked by the jsdelivr bot, so I simply updated the website. Still, don't know what happened here, so your insight will be valuable @vvo.\n",
